---
@META
dir: skillsPraut/src/components/backgrounds/
updated: 2026-04-09
files: 11
stack: React, Remotion, TypeScript, SVG, Canvas

@EXPORTS
CircuitPattern.tsx: CircuitPattern — SVG circuit-board pattern in low-opacity blue
GradientMesh.tsx: GradientMesh — animated radial gradient navy/purple/blue
GridBackground.tsx: GridBackground — tech grid with configurable cell size
NavyBackground.tsx: NavyBackground — flat frame.bg (#060818)
NoiseOverlay.tsx: NoiseOverlay — SVG turbulence film grain at 3% opacity
ParticleField.tsx: ParticleField — deterministic drifting blue particles
ScanlineEffect.tsx: ScanlineEffect — CRT scanline bands overlay
SpaceNebula.tsx: SpaceNebula — animated nebula clouds + stars (subtle|medium|dramatic)
SpiralGalaxy.tsx: SpiralGalaxy — canvas density-wave galaxy (~6000 stars)
StarField.tsx: StarField — twinkling star pinpricks
VignetteOverlay.tsx: VignetteOverlay — radial corner darkening

@FUNCTIONS
SpiralGalaxy() → React.FC
  purpose: canvas galaxy background for frames
  side-effects: none (canvas render per frame)

SpaceNebula({intensity,loopFrames,flyThrough}) → React.FC
  purpose: animated nebula with configurable intensity
  side-effects: none

@DEPENDENCIES
internal: styles/tokens (colors, frame, withOpacity) | hooks/interpolateColors
external: remotion (AbsoluteFill, useCurrentFrame, useVideoConfig)

@STANDARDS
- SpiralGalaxy is the DEFAULT background for PrautVideoFrame
- All backgrounds use deterministic seeded random — stable across renders
- Overlays (Noise, Scanline, Vignette) use pointerEvents: "none"
- All colors from tokens — no hardcoded hex
---
